Nonbreeding adult.description: Double-crested Cormorants are smaller than Great Cormorants. Nonbreeding birds have an orange chin and dark throat whereas nonbreeding Great Cormorants have a yellow chin and white throat.

Breeding adult.description: Double-crested Cormorants are smaller than Great Cormorants. They have a darker face, a thinner bill, and a thinner neck than Great Cormorants, which have a whiter face and a thicker bill and neck.

Juvenile.description: Juvenile Double-crested Cormorants have paler throat and a dingier belly than juvenile Great Cormorants, which have a darker neck and paler belly.
